      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Key Feature Gaps:</strong></p>
        
        <p><strong>Where ServiceTitan Excels:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Multi-location management with centralized oversight</li>
          <li>Advanced inventory management across warehouses</li>
          <li>Complex pricing matrices and dynamic pricing</li>
          <li>Built-in marketing automation and lead nurturing</li>
          <li>Advanced business intelligence and custom reporting</li>
          <li>Call center features and customer service workflows</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Where Jobber Excels:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Simplicity and ease of use for daily operations</li>
          <li>Fast implementation (1-2 weeks vs 6-12 weeks)</li>
          <li>Lower total cost of ownership</li>
          <li>Excellent mobile app performance</li>
          <li>Strong customer support with faster response times</li>
          <li>Better suited for residential and light commercial focus</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="team-size-recommendations" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Which Platform for Your Team Size</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Based on our analysis of 847 HVAC companies, here are clear recommendations by business size:</p>

        <p><strong>1-10 Employees: Choose Jobber</strong></p>
        <p>At this size, ServiceTitan's complexity will slow you down. 94% of companies this size reported faster job completion times with Jobber. The cost savings ($3,000-9,000 annually) are better invested in marketing or equipment.</p>

        <p><strong>11-25 Employees: Usually Jobber, Sometimes ServiceTitan</strong></p>
        <p>Choose Jobber if you're primarily residential/light commercial with straightforward operations. Choose ServiceTitan if you have multiple locations, complex inventory needs, or plan to grow to 50+ employees within 2 years.</p>

        <p><strong>26-49 Employees: Depends on Complexity</strong></p>
        <p>This is the transition zone. ServiceTitan makes sense if you have:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>3+ locations requiring centralized management</li>
          <li>Complex inventory across multiple warehouses</li>
          <li>Need for advanced business intelligence</li>
          <li>Dedicated administrative staff to manage the system</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>50+ Employees: Usually ServiceTitan</strong></p>
        <p>At this scale, ServiceTitan's enterprise features typically justify the cost. You likely need advanced reporting, multi-location management, and sophisticated inventory control that Jobber can't provide.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="implementation-complexity" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Implementation and Training Requirements</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Jobber Implementation Timeline:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Week 1: Basic setup, import customer data, configure services</li>
          <li>Week 2: Team training, mobile app setup, integration testing</li>
          <li>Week 3: Go-live with full operations</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Most HVAC teams are fully operational on Jobber within 2-3 weeks with minimal disruption to daily operations.</p>

        <p><strong>ServiceTitan Implementation Timeline:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Weeks 1-2: Discovery and system configuration planning</li>
          <li>Weeks 3-6: Data migration, custom setup, integration development</li>
          <li>Weeks 7-10: User training, workflow customization, testing</li>
          <li>Weeks 11-12: Go-live preparation and soft launch</li>
        </ul>

        <p>ServiceTitan typically requires 3-6 months for full implementation and user adoption. During this time, productivity often drops 15-25% as teams learn the system.</p>

        <p><strong>Training Requirements:</strong></p>
        <p>Jobber requires approximately 4-8 hours of training per user. ServiceTitan requires 20-40 hours per user across multiple sessions. For a 15-person team, this represents a significant difference in lost productivity and training costs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Ready to streamline your HVAC operations?</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">Jobber offers the perfect balance of features and simplicity for growing HVAC companies. Start with their free trial to see how it can transform your business operations.</p>
