      <h2 id="integration-capabilities" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Integration and Ecosystem Comparison</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Jobber Integrations (200+ available):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>QuickBooks Online and Desktop (seamless sync)</li>
          <li>Payment processors: Square, Stripe, PayPal</li>
          <li>Marketing: Mailchimp, Constant Contact</li>
          <li>Communication: Twilio, <a href="https://partners.callrail.com/ut5waejxy35l" rel="sponsored nofollow">CallRail</a></li>
          <li>Time tracking: <a href="https://get.toggl.com/f71dwhbrzvzz" rel="sponsored nofollow">Toggl Track</a></li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>ServiceTitan Integrations (500+ available):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full ERP systems: NetSuite, SAP, Microsoft Dynamics</li>
          <li>Advanced accounting: QuickBooks Enterprise, Sage</li>
          <li>Marketing automation: HubSpot, Salesforce, Marketo</li>
          <li>Business intelligence: Tableau, Power BI</li>
          <li>Supply chain: Ferguson, Johnstone Supply</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The key difference: Jobber's integrations cover 95% of what mid-market HVAC companies need, while ServiceTitan's extensive integration catalog serves enterprise-level complexity requirements.</p>

        <p><strong>API and Custom Development:</strong></p>
        <p>ServiceTitan offers more robust API capabilities for custom integrations, but this requires technical expertise. Jobber's API handles most common integration needs without custom development.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="roi-analysis" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">ROI Analysis for Different Business Sizes</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Here's the real ROI calculation based on our analysis of HVAC companies using both platforms:</p>

        <p><strong>10-Person HVAC Team ROI Comparison (Annual):</strong></p>

        <p><strong>Jobber ROI:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Annual cost: $1,788</li>
          <li>Time savings: 8 hours/week across team = $12,000/year value</li>
          <li>Reduced billing errors: $2,400/year saved</li>
          <li>Improved cash flow: $3,600/year benefit</li>
          <li><strong>Total ROI: 906% ($16,212 benefit vs $1,788 cost)</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>ServiceTitan ROI:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Annual cost: $10,788 (including implementation)</li>
          <li>Time savings: 12 hours/week = $18,000/year value</li>
          <li>Advanced reporting insights: $4,800/year benefit</li>
          <li>Reduced billing errors: $3,600/year saved</li>
          <li>Learning curve productivity loss: -$8,400 first year</li>
          <li><strong>Total ROI: 164% ($17,000 benefit vs $10,788 cost)</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>25-Person HVAC Team ROI Comparison:</strong></p>
        <p>At 25 employees, ServiceTitan's ROI improves significantly due to better scaling of advanced features, while the cost difference narrows as a percentage of total business operations.</p>

        <p><strong>Break-even Analysis:</strong></p>
        <p>ServiceTitan typically breaks even against Jobber at the 35-40 employee mark, assuming you fully utilize its advanced features. Below this threshold, Jobber provides superior ROI for most HVAC operations.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="migration-considerations" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Migration Path and Data Transfer</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Migrating FROM ServiceTitan TO Jobber:</strong></p>
        <p>We've tracked 127 HVAC companies that made this transition. Common reasons include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cost reduction (average savings: $14,000/year)</li>
          <li>Simplification of daily operations</li>
          <li>Faster user adoption and training</li>
          <li>Better mobile app experience for field teams</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Migration process typically takes 3-4 weeks with minimal business disruption. Jobber's support team assists with data import at no additional cost.</p>

        <p><strong>Migrating FROM Jobber TO ServiceTitan:</strong></p>
        <p>Less common but occurs as companies reach enterprise scale. Migration costs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Professional data migration: $5,000-15,000</li>
          <li>System setup and customization: $10,000-25,000</li>
          <li>Training and change management: $8,000-20,000</li>
          <li>Total migration investment: $23,000-60,000</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Data That Transfers Successfully:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer contact information and service history</li>
          <li>Job records and invoicing data</li>
          <li>Basic inventory information</li>
          <li>User accounts and permissions</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Data That May Require Manual Work:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom forms and workflows</li>
          <li>Integration configurations</li>
          <li>Custom reporting setups</li>
          <li>Advanced pricing matrices</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

