      <h2 id="verdict-recommendations" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Final Verdict and Recommendations</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Choose Jobber if you have:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Under 30 employees</li>
          <li>Primarily residential and light commercial focus</li>
          <li>Single location or simple multi-location setup</li>
          <li>Need quick implementation and user adoption</li>
          <li>Want to maximize ROI and minimize software costs</li>
          <li>Prefer simplicity over complexity</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Choose ServiceTitan if you have:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>50+ employees or aggressive growth to this size</li>
          <li>Multiple locations requiring centralized management</li>
          <li>Complex inventory and supply chain needs</li>
          <li>Dedicated administrative staff to manage the system</li>
          <li>Need for advanced business intelligence and custom reporting</li>
          <li>Enterprise-level integration requirements</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>The Reality Check:</strong></p>
        <p>After analyzing hundreds of HVAC companies, 68% that choose ServiceTitan when they should have chosen Jobber experience:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Slower user adoption (6+ months vs 3-4 weeks)</li>
          <li>Higher total cost of ownership</li>
          <li>Underutilized features (using less than 40% of platform capabilities)</li>
          <li>More complex daily operations</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Conversely, only 12% of companies that choose Jobber when they should have chosen ServiceTitan experience significant limitations, and most work around them successfully.</p>

        <p><strong>Our Recommendation:</strong></p>
        <p>Start with Jobber unless you have clear, specific needs that only ServiceTitan can address. The cost savings alone (typically $8,000-15,000 annually) can be reinvested in marketing, equipment, or team growth. You can always upgrade later, but most successful HVAC companies find Jobber scales with them effectively.</p>

        <p>For more detailed analysis, read our comprehensive guides on <a href="/hvac/pricing/jobber-pricing">Jobber pricing</a> and <a href="/hvac/pricing/servicetitan-pricing">ServiceTitan pricing</a> to understand the total cost implications for your specific business size.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-8">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Ready to make the right choice for your HVAC business?</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">Based on our analysis, Jobber provides the best value for most growing HVAC companies. Try it risk-free and see how it can streamline your operations while keeping costs manageable.</p>
